  "duration": 24.939,
  "text": "An analogy: imagine trying to hear someone whisper in a noisy room. If they say one quick word, you might miss it. If they stretch that same word out over 32 times longer, repeating the same acoustic pattern slowly, your brain has much more time to accumulate evidence of the pattern and filter out the noise. The message content is identical \u2014 you just gave yourself more integration time to be sure of what you heard."
